<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR> My purpose here on the boards is to have a little fun poking at the people that have double standards and just give them a good razzing.  <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Sooo your purpose here is that of a troll?<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR> The whole issue of new spells, or new skills is all wishful thinking for the most part as that will never happen. What I find the most humorous about these boards are people like Tan, Nic and Sshadow that have virtually cut down ever option anyone has made saying it OVERPOWERS the beastlord.<BR> <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>The options that they have cut down were ridiculous and wouldn't improve beastlords in any meaningful way.  So far all they have shot down (to my memory and I will admit it isn't the best) is us getting fd, and your ideas.<P>Now on fd, we don't need this skill.  If they gave us full fd at a 200 cap then monks would riot.  Imagine playing a rogue and then all of a sudden they gave warriors the ability to backstab.  That is very similar to what giving us fd would be.  Ok, so give us a lower cap fd.  This wouldn't help us find groups easier, since we can't pull with it.  It wouldn' help us on raids for the same reason, and it being unreliable wouldn't be much help on a cr.  It wouldn't help us solo, since it is unreliable to use to break a camp, doesn't increase our offense in any way, and doesn't really improve us.  The only time when fd would be useful at a lowered cap is when we do something stupid.  We could then recover from being stupid.  I for one believe in Darwinism and am therefore against saveing people from their own stupidity.  Saveing us from our own stupidity is not much of a class improvement.  But it could be used by Verant as a reason to not fix any of our real problems.<P>Now on to your ideas.  I don't think they are overpowering.  I won't lie to you, I think they are stupid.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" fa