Yes. Gordon stayed and Brad & Jeff left. There was also hint that a few of the key programmers (nameless)have left or will be leaving as well.  It is my opinion that the game is changing in direction that the orinators are not happy with, and I don't blame them. You talk about class balance, however you don't acknowledge some of the changes in the game as being unbalancing.<P>Fear Immunity = making pets safer in high level dungeons? Does this not unbalance the tanking class to where they are more reliable then a pet?  Afterall, again you argue RISK with everything.  It's a risk I take to go in dungeons without SoW, correct? So how is that Risk different then the risk of a Caster taking his pet into zones where FEAR is a deffinate possibilty?<P>Soul Binders = Was a direct stepping on toes of every binding class.  You talk about hide/sneak/FD/ID stepping on the toes of those classes that have those skill or abilites.  However by adding soul binders you have taken away from those classes that sometimes relay on that for income durring off times when not adventuring.  Granted a high level binder could care less about 10pp donation for a bid.  BUT a much lower level newbie just starting the game that is so maybe 8th level has been deprived of that possiblity. And you don't call this unbalancing?  What's next to come SoW binders NPC's in every other zone for those that want SoW, but can't find anyone to cast it on them.  <P>Nexus ports = A neccessity for the game to get to luclin however, there was only to be  a couple of these in the innitial design. Before the game came out more where added so that a total of 4 were implimented. More then orignally desired.  Now once again they added a Nexus port to the Great Divide.  Was this stepping on the toes or unbalancing?  You bet damn right it was.  By doing this a VAST LARGE number Druids and Wizzies were deprived of their income oppurtunity in GD and Thurg by those that wanted to get to Luclin and would have had to get port to a location near a nexus portal.  I have been in the GD many and many times over and the income potential for a porting class was easily in the range of 100's of plat a day, maybe even a 1,000.   This definately stepped on a CLASS definning skill that only 2 have (druids/wizzies) and yet most don't complain.  <P>This also hurt standard ports as well, because many now that wish not to donate for ports to DL (kunark) can simply take the Nexus up and back down to Kunark.  BTW, just incase you feel like claiming that no one wants to wait 15 minutes to go up and then 15 minutes to come back as an option, this would be wrong.  Yes all nexus ports are on a approx 15-20 minute timer. That would be the longest amout of time to wait if you were unlucky to miss the port, if not.. much less.. My average wait is 8 minutes or so. Another fact all returning ports from luclin back to Norrath are 5 minutes after you arrive, so this way you would not have to wait for another 15 minutes.  This was planned for the exact purpose of getting someone from ONE nexus port to another with a wait of NO longer then 20 minutes.  And I know that there are times that people would wait longer then that to find druid/wizzy ports in /ooc...<P>So far the changes yet (aka Brad & Jeff leaving) are not positive on class balancing and if VI is persistant about continuing to make more changes they may end up screwing up the entire class balancing system if they are not careful.<BR>--------------------------------------------<P>OK enough of philosophy on EQ..  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>The only physical changes that I would like to see in the game is reasonable quest that reward something worth while and TRADESKILLS.<P>I'm a masterbaker, masterfletcher, mastersmith, masterfisher, and worthing on close to 100 in tailoring and brewing.  These skills have virtually nothing to do with class unbalancing and "stepping" on toes and are very fun, or atleast they used to be. Since all the expansion they have made these trade skill extremely time consuming and frustrating.  Only 1/2 of the people on EQ can even be eligable for Cutural Skills, while others are left outside looking in and not able to do anything.  The only thing tradeskills might have done would be to lower the market value on armor and weapons if they did, which has NO effect on class balancing.  I would like to see all tradeskill made significantly easier to achieve PAST 150 and over 200 espeically.<P>BTW with the release of vendor bought horses, wasn't that a direct UNBALANCING of classes giving virtually all Class the ability of Jboots/SoW/or faster speeds? It sure looks that way to me.  What is next?  I know a Vendor that teaches you the art of Body Control and Meditation.  You pay him 50K in plat and he teaches you to Feign Death.. hahahahaha  or to meditate at the same rate as C2... hahahahaha
