ly.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Wouldn't that defeat the purpose?  Then anyone could easily achieve a 250 skill and cheapens the whole concept of tradeskills being something that takes time, skill, and devotion.  There would be no need to seek out a 200+ skill tailor (and they are rare).<P>BTW, this whining about tradeskills has nothing to do with beastlords.  You should really take this to the <a href="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=forum&f=1">General Discussion</a> forum.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>BTW with the release of vendor bought horses, wasn't that a direct UNBALANCING of classes giving virtually all Class the ability of Jboots/SoW/or faster speeds?<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Not really, there are too many drawbacks to horses for them to be anything but a means of travel.  Even then, SoW/Jboots/Tboots are far superior (you are aware that horses don't work indoors, yes?  You are aware that horses disappear when you zone, yes?)  Horses are really nothing more than a luxury item, a flashy thing to show off.<P>Please take your general EQ trolling to the general forums.  This forum is for the discussion of beastlords.<P>--------------------<P>"Talk sense to a fool and he will call you foolish."   - Euripides
