You know what I find interesting about the poster here.  He writes a topic, and asks to not be flamed..ok.  Some people pose some arguement to what he posts...some interjection.  He then reiterates that he doesn't want any flames..only good solid feedback.  <P>See, I had read the replies, and they weren't flames, they just weren't agreeing with you.  You should have re-worded what you were asking for.  You should have said, "If you do not agree with me, don't post here..I'm only looking to get more ideas or improve on these.la la la".  People weren't flaming you, they were disagreeing with you.  They may have flamed you afterwards, I have no clue, I didn't want to read through it all, and if they did, all power to them.<P>I wanna give you a heads up on the higher level raiding environment.  You could have a successful raid with only clerics and warriors..maybe throw in some rogues and one monk to pull.  Thats all you need.  Healing, tanking, damage.  The rest is utility.  You can disagree with me all you want, but how many of you in the higher lvl game have seen a raid called off because there weren't enough druids?  How bout paladins...no?  Ever see a raid called cause there were no wizards there? (though lvl 60 wizards are amazing to behold..a raid can be done without them)  Oh wait, I had a raid cancelled one time cause we didn't have any rangers...oh wait..no I didn't.  NOW I HAVE gone to raids that were cancelled cause we didn't have any/enough warriors or enough clerics..thats the fact.  The reason not everyone plays clerics, warriors, and rogues is because not everyone enjoys them as much as they enjoy the others.  The others play a utility role, some better than others, and this will be where the BST fits in.  Y'all will be given some buffs that will stack with everything and give great stats...like pallys and rangers etc.. got.  It will be something that will make a raid want a BST, but I promise you that a raid will never NEED a BST.<P>Now for exp groups...if someone doesn't get you in it, its because they're the type of people that always want the "perfect" group.  You know what I love about those people..they're the same people that are *****ing now when a couple of wizards and mages go down to Disco 1 and 2 in Seb and kill every frog around.  Those are the same wizards and mages they left sitting at the zone in LFG because they didn't fit into their perfect little scheme.  If they're not taking you into their groups, then take their groups away from them.  I will say one thing, the wizards that started taking the exp camps from the perfect cleric/warrior/enchanter/rogue/insert any other two, weren't the ones on the boards posting about what more VI could give them, they were the ones wondering what more they could do with what they have.....<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61037" TARGET=_blank>Tomlyn Drayke-Lvl 60 Arch Mage</A><BR>Fallken Stallken-Lvl 29 Rogue<BR>Prexus<P>"I knew it!  I'm surrounded by *******s"  Dark Helmet - Spaceballs
