Well I have to disagree with you there Sshadow.  Without our pets we are very gimped.  Moreso then mages, and moreso then necros.  Not to the point of uselessnes, but as I stated above I would guess around 30%.  The pet is a large contributor of our damage and I would estimate that half of our spells are pet only.<P>To graatzer, if savagery last 6 minutes, and has a 3 minute recast time, then you can keep 2 people buffed with savagery.  Sure they will have to go a few second without savagery every 6 minutes, but haveing 2 people with it is better then one (although I still wish to murder whoever gave it a peridot component.  Nothing that lasts as short as savagery should cost me a peridot   <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0">   ).<P>To get back to what Rydeson posted, I would like to express my ideas (probably borrowed from someone else) on how to fix the beastlord class.<P>1.  A spell, usable at 55th level at the earliest, that makes pets immune to fear.<P>2.  Resist buffs that add 120 to our pets resistances.  These should stack with the resistnce line and possibly any other resistance buffs that stack with that.  If I remember my resist line attainment levels correctly, fire and poison should be gotten at 56, cold and disease at 58, and magic at 60.  (note:  these spells would also have to be (and should be) given to necromancers and mages.  Maybe shamans as well.)<P>These 2 fixes would help us when we NEED them.  That is on the high level raids.  They are reasonable because other classes of these levels can achieve such  high resists.  I don't see any good reason for our pets to not as well, since we can not improve them with gear.  They wouldn't be IMMUNE to the AE's, but then neither is anyone else.<P>I personally am against a fix for the ripostes problem.  Everyone but people who don't melee must deal with these.  The only thing I can say is hope you are quick with /pet back off command when the mob suddenly turns the same way your pet is facing.  If you can get your friendly neighborhood cleric (and most clerics are friendly and neighborly) to cast a couple hit point buffs on your pet, he should be able to survive one round of ripostes.<P>Oh and of course, I would like to see the pathing fixed.  /pet guard here combined with summon companion won't help if a wanderer jumps your mob as you are moveing.  Don't know how common that is though.
