Dalfayen Blightfighter,<P>We can agree to disagree on this point if you like. It is a contestable statement either way though. Mage pets can make up a very significant portion of mage damage, especially in raid situations. On Raid-MOBs where the resist rate on non-lure spells are very high (and in some cases 100%), a pet would make up almost all of a Mage&#8217;s damage.<P>In any case, either side of the argument could be correct in differing circumstances. My argument with the great Rydeson was simply that it couldn&#8217;t be stated as an uncontested fact.<P>Those ideas on how to fix the class mirror some that I posted on another thread (and have sent to Verant). We are in agreement on this except that I also argued for some fashion in which to address the riposte issue. We can also agree to disagree on this if you like, since we agree in most other areas. I simply think that the near-impossibility of keeping a pet positioned behind a MOB in many situations should be offset with something. Perhaps with a command that helps to accomplish pet positioning or something. Immunity is not the only fix but I do believe there is a problem here.<P>Again, we can agree to disagree. The 2 fixes we do agree on would help us, and other pet classes, immensely.<P>I maintain that the raid issues we have are not so much BST issues, as general pet-class issues.<P>--------------------<P>Balance doesn&#8217;t always mean you getting more and/or others getting less. Sometimes you have to recognize that you should be the one to not get more, or to give something up.
